# Software cache — large binaries staged here for VM provisioning
# Run scripts/cache-software.sh to populate from the manifest.
#
# scanner-cache/ holds first-build artifacts (openssl 3.5 binary tree, CBOM-Lens
# Go binary, cloned source repos). The role tasks populate this on first cold-build;
# subsequent cold-builds skip the source-build step in favor of the cached artifact.
# wsus-cache/ is the WSUS golden master: SUSDB.mdf + SUSDB_log.ldf (catalog DB) AND
# WsusContent/ (patch binaries, ~118 GB). All ignored by wsus-cache/* below; only the
# .gitkeep + README.md are committed (~30 min savings on cold-builds after the first).
# Cache files themselves are gitignored — only the directory marker is committed.
*
!.gitignore
!sbom.json
!Straylight-*.json
!template-aliases.json
!kb-pins.txt
!choco/
!scanner-cache/
scanner-cache/*
!scanner-cache/.gitkeep
!scanner-cache/README.md
!wsus-cache/
wsus-cache/*
!wsus-cache/.gitkeep
!wsus-cache/README.md
!gnupg-cache/
gnupg-cache/*
!gnupg-cache/.gitkeep
!gnupg-cache/README.md
